"title": "6717: reconciliation, of the world to God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6717",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>On account of sin, people are alienated from God and cut off from fellowship with him. Through Jesus Christ, God reconciles the world to himself, breaking down the barriers of hostility and estrangement.</p>\n<h2>A broken relationship through sin brings alienation from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23-Gen3:24\">GEN 3:23–3:24</a> <em>the expulsion from Eden</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:13-Gen4:14\">GEN 4:13–4:14</a> <em>Cain's alienation from God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:22\">ISA 48:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:5\">JER 33:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13\">LUK 18:13</a> <em>the tax collector's prayer for mercy</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:10\">ROM 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:7\">ROM 8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:3\">EPH 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:12\">EPH 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18\">EPH 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21\">COL 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>God takes the initiative in bringing about reconciliation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6-Rom5:8\">ROM 5:6–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>The means of reconciliation is the death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6\">ROM 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13\">EPH 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:16\">EPH 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20\">COL 1:20</a></p>\n<h2>The results of reconciliation are both personal and universal</h2>\n<h3>Peace with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1\">ROM 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:36-Acts10:46\">ACT 10:36–10:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:19\">EPH 2:14–2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21-Col1:22\">COL 1:21–1:22</a></p>\n<h3>Access to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:2\">ROM 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:12\">EPH 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>Adoption as God's children</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:16\">ROM 8:15–8:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:6\">GAL 4:4–4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1-1John3:2\">1JN 3:1–3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Peacemaking throughout the universe</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20\">COL 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:15\">ROM 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:7–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22-Eph1:23\">EPH 1:22–1:23</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are to be the ambassadors of reconciliation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:18–5:20</a></strong></p>",
